250 g Ground Beef
¾ cup Jasmine Rice
56 g Carrot, julienned
1 tbsp Garlic Puree
1 unit(s) Shanghai Bok Choy
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
2 tsp Sriracha
2 tbsp Soy Sauce
1 tbsp Sesame Oil
2 unit(s) Green Onion
113 g Sugar Snap Peas
¼ tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add rice to the boiling water. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, thinly slice green onions.
Trim snap peas.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add sesame oil, then beef, garlic puree and half the green onions. Cook, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 3-4 min.** Season with salt and pepper.
Add 1 1/2 tbsp (3 tbsp) soy sauce. Cook, stirring often, until beef is coated, 1-2 min.

Add snap peas to the pan with beef. Cook, stirring often, until tender-crisp, 3-4 min.
Add carrots and bok choy. Cook, stirring often, until tender-crisp, 1-2 min. Season with salt and pepper, to taste.
Remove the pan from heat.

St ir together mayo, 1 tsp (2 tsp) soy sauce and sriracha in a small bowl. Set aside.

Fluff rice with a fork, then stir in remaining green onions. Season with salt, to taste.
Divide rice between plates.
Top with beef-veggie mixture.
Drizzle sriracha mayo over top.

Heat the same pan (from step 3) over medium. When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then crack in two eggs (4 for 4 ppl). Season with salt and pepper.
Pan-fry covered until whites are set, 2-3 min.** (NOTE: The yolks will still be runny.)
Top bowls with eggs!

If you've opted to get beef, cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the turkey.